                           *** INTRODUCTION ***

 For many years now hacking in the Amiga scene has just been an every day
thing. It has become so normal that most people find it funny when someone
complains about it especially the people who have been in the scene for a
long time. I myself have been with the Amiga since the A500 was released
and so I have seen many groups, people and boards come and go. Now things
are changing rapidly in the scene. I see new guys come into the scene all
new and shinny that stick out like sore thumbs and I see that they do not
respect the people at the other end, the time and effort that people put
into their productions are just ignored. The new guys think that cracking
and hacking is the best way to go into the scene and they are the ones that
are destroying it. Because of this our boards and our best people are being
busted, is this the way to go? Is this the future - a dead machine? All I
ask is that you respect your scene members, you might never see them or
ever speak to them besides keyboard chatter but give credit to were credit
is deserved and support the scene. Just because you may receive this file
does not mean to say that you should go around ripping peoples work and
spreading it like wild fire. This file is ONLY for personal interest and is
not for profit making schemes or world famous acknowledgment.
 __________________________________________________________________________
 __________________________________________________________________________

 From what I have seen to this date I believe that this text file posseses
more information than any other, it has been intensly researched and
updated every now and again to keep up with the times. This is the fourth
version of this file so as you can guess it always grows and expands like
most information does in this technological era. Because of this I would
like to state (again) that this information is only for your personal
interest and not for commercial or personal gain in or outside the scene.

 Because a group called Infect have produced a ripper of high standard I
have given permission for this file to be released with it and only with
it. Both time and effort have been put into the ripper and with this file
and so all I ask is that you support it by becoming a registered user. I
myself am not getting anything from it and I do not intend to or want to
because I support the scene with my own money and my own time. But I would
like all you guys out there that are interested in ripping to register a
copy no matter if you have a hacked copy of the registered version or a
copy of the unregistered version.

 Some of the guys that recieved or got hold of previous versions will
realise that the name of the file has changed and that everything has
become Amiga Guide friendly. The reasons for this are as follows:

 The name change - I really thought after the first two releases that the
name Module Ripping For Professionals was very, very corny. I mean if they
were pro's why would they want to read the file? Also it was not indepth as
a professional ripper would have liked it to be, here I am only skimming
the surface of a very complex and time consuming task so all the decent
rippers were and still are not gaining anything from this file!

 Amiga Guide - Need I even give you my reasons for this? Come on, it's the
way to go and why not take advantage of a good tool like that? Support the
AMIGA not those PC's!
 __________________________________________________________________________
